1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:09,140
Start with identity and location. whoami, hostname, pwd, and HOME prove which account, system, and working directory this terminal controls before we make any change.

2
00:00:09,490 --> 00:00:19,310
The os-release file describes Ubuntu user space. uname reports the running kernel and machine architecture, while ps confirms that systemd is process one. These are related facts, not one version number.

3
00:00:19,660 --> 00:00:31,320
We build system-profile.txt from the observed commands instead of typing guessed values. The second evidence file maps configuration, persistent logs, and runtime state to their standard filesystem locations.

4
00:00:31,670 --> 00:00:42,970
The final test proves that all three directories exist, then cat displays both evidence files. The checker validates every required key and confirms that the profile describes the current seat.
